📄 Product Requirements Document (PRD)

🧩 Product Name (Working)

OnTrack AI

⸻

1. 🎯 Problem Statement

Teams consistently fail to deliver on expected timelines—not due to lack of effort, but due to:

* Mismatch between planned vs actual work
* Scope creep during execution
* Unforeseen disruptions (infra downtime, performance issues, leave)
* Delayed visibility into problems

Root Cause:

Project tracking relies on manual updates, which are:

* Incomplete
* Delayed
* Biased

As a result:

* Teams only realize delays too late
* Decisions are reactive, not proactive

⸻

2. 💡 Product Vision

A self-updating execution system that automatically captures work activity and continuously recomputes project timelines using AI.

The system:

* Eliminates manual updates
* Builds ground truth of execution
* Dynamically adjusts expectations in real time
* Learns from historical data to improve future planning

⸻

3. 🧠 Core Principles

1. Zero Friction Capture

Users should not need to manually update progress.

2. Ground Truth Over Reported Truth

System relies on actual activity signals, not self-reported status.

3. Continuous Recalculation

Project timelines are not static — they evolve with reality.

4. AI as Reasoning Engine

AI explains:

* What changed
* Why it changed
* What to do next

5. Compounding Intelligence

Past projects improve future estimation and planning.

⸻

4. 👤 Target Users (Hackathon Scope)

Primary:

* Software Developers
* Engineering Teams

Secondary (Future):

* Product Managers
* Operations Teams
* Non-technical knowledge workers (via tool integrations)

⸻

5. ⚙️ Core Features

⸻

5.1 Passive Activity Capture (MCP Layer)

Description:

Automatically capture daily work without manual input.

Inputs:

* Git commits
* Pull requests
* Local dev activity (via MCP hooks)
* Task metadata (mock Jira / backlog)

Output:

* Auto-generated daily changelog
* Structured activity logs

⸻

5.2 AI Activity Summarisation

Description:

Convert raw activity into meaningful daily updates.

Output:

* What was worked on
* What progressed
* What changed
* Emerging blockers (if detectable)

⸻

5.3 Execution Understanding Engine

Description:

AI reconstructs project state by comparing:

* Planned work (tasks, scope)
* Actual work (captured activity)

Output:

* Task progress mapping
* Velocity trends
* Scope changes detected

⸻

5.4 Dynamic Timeline Recalculation (Core Feature)

Description:

Continuously recompute project timeline based on:

* Actual velocity
* Scope changes
* Disruptions (e.g., leave, downtime)

Output:

* Updated delivery estimate
* Delay prediction (if any)
* Acceleration opportunities (if possible)

⸻

5.5 Deviation Detection & Explanation

Description:

Detect when execution deviates from plan and explain why.

Output Examples:

* “Project delayed by 2 days due to increased scope (+30%)”
* “Velocity dropped due to infra downtime”
* “Auth module taking longer due to performance debugging”

⸻

5.6 AI Recommendations

Description:

Suggest actionable next steps.

Output:

* Extend timeline
* Reduce scope
* Reallocate resources
* Parallelize tasks

⸻

5.7 Execution Timeline View (Not Just Dashboard)

Description:

Unified, AI-generated view of project state.

Displays:

* Current status (On-track / Off-track)
* Timeline evolution
* Key events:
    * Scope changes
    * Velocity shifts
    * Blockers

⸻

5.8 Historical Intelligence Layer

Description:

Store completed project data for future learning.

Capabilities:

* Cross-project analysis
* Pattern detection:
    * “Tasks of type X take 30% longer”
* Improved future estimation

⸻

6. 🔄 User Flow (Developer - Hackathon Version)

Step 1:

Developer works normally (commits, PRs)

Step 2:

MCP captures activity automatically

Step 3:

System generates daily changelog

Step 4:

AI summarises and interprets activity

Step 5:

System updates:

* Project status
* Timeline projection

Step 6:

User views:

* “On track / Off track”
* Reasons
* Suggested actions

⸻

7. 🧪 Demo Scenario (Hackathon)

Setup:

* Project planned: 5 features in 7 days

Simulated Inputs:

* Reduced commit frequency
* Scope increase (new feature added)
* Dev inactivity (leave / downtime)

Expected Output:

* System flags delay
* Explains:
    * Scope increase
    * Velocity drop
* Suggests:
    * Timeline extension OR scope reduction

⸻

8. 🏗️ Technical Architecture (High-Level)

Input Layer:

* MCP hooks (dev activity)
* Mock task data (JSON)

Processing Layer:

* LLM (Claude) for:
    * Summarisation
    * Reasoning
    * Deviation detection

Logic Layer:

* Timeline estimation engine
* Velocity tracking
* Scope change detection

Output Layer:

* API / UI
* Timeline view
* Status indicators

⸻

